 Add drained noodles, hot water, mushrooms, soy sauce, salt, pepper and remaining 2 teaspoons miso paste to mixing bowl and cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Meanwhile, transfer salmon onto prepared baking tray and bake for 7 minutes (200°C). Set remaining glaze aside."},{"content":"Add bok choy to mixing bowl and cook <b>4 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Remove salmon from oven. Turn oven setting to grill and carefully move oven rack to upper part of oven. Brush salmon with remaining reserved glaze and place under pre-heated grill for 2-3 minutes, until surface blackens and salmon is cooked to your liking. Flake salmon into bite-size pieces."},{"content":"Divide soup between serving bowls and top with salmon. Garnish with spring onions\/shallots and sprinkle with black sesame seeds (optional) to serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["We used a dried sweet potato noodle for this recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","4 portions"]}